folder: Brielle Avenue & Rockland Avenue, Staten Island, NY
text:
Brielle Avenue, adjoining the N.W. corner of Rockland Avenue, showing an abandoned stone house. It appears on Beers's 1874 map as a schoolhouse. It was later on the Garlich (Garlish) property.
View 1: November 3, 1912
View 2: April 5, 1924
By Wm T. Davis through P. L. Sperr
